parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates without pressing the accelerator pedal
the vehicle hesitates or jerks when pressing the accelerator pedal
the vehicle accelerates abnormally even when the brake pedal is pressed
the vehicle continues to accelerate despite attempts to slow down or stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the horn can lead to a lack of auditory warning, potentially causing accidents or near-misses, especially in emergency situations.
symptoms: The horn does not produce any sound or produces a weak sound when pressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Paint flaking or defects can lead to rust and corrosion, compromising the structural integrity of the vehicle and potentially affecting its overall appearance and resale value.
symptoms: Paint flaking
peeling
or cracking
especially on new vehicles with low mileage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lack of summary information or incomplete records can make it difficult for owners to identify and address potential issues, potentially leading to safety risks or maintenance problems.
symptoms: No summary information available for the vehicle
incomplete records
or missing data.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden acceleration and brake failure can lead to loss of control, accidents, and injuries. The failure of airbags to deploy properly can exacerbate the severity of injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly
brakes do not respond or fail to engage
cruise control-like feeling
inability to stop the vehicle
airbags do not deploy or deploy improperly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Improper airbag deployment can lead to inadequate protection in the event of an accident, resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Airbags underinflate
airbags do not deploy
airbags deploy improperly
failure of airbags to provide adequate protection.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake system failure can lead to loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Brakes do not respond or fail to engage
brakes feel soft or spongy
inability to stop the vehicle
brake lights do not illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the automatic door closing system can cause the rear side passenger door to be incapable of securely being closed, posing a serious hazard to passengers, other traffic, and the possibility of the door coming completely off the body of the car.
symptoms: The door cannot be shut even manually
the door flops open and closed while driving
the door may come completely off the body of the car.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the trunk lifters can cause the trunk to strike the operator, resulting in physical harm.
symptoms: The trunk strikes the operator
the trunk does not stay open
the trunk can only be held open with a cane.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the wheels can cause the tires to go flat while driving, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The wheels accumulate corrosion
the tires go flat while driving
the vehicle experiences a loss of control.
